cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.SY

This paper is likely to belong to the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it presents a framework for unsupervised learning of representations. It also involves the use of neural networks, which is a common technique in machine learning. 

It could also belong to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) as it specifically focuses on learning via neural populations. 

cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another likely sub-category as the paper involves the development of an algorithm for unsupervised learning, which is a common task in AI. 

cs.CV (Computer Vision) is also a possibility as the paper mentions the method works for extracting salient features from input datasets, which is a common task in computer vision. 

Finally, cs.SY (Systems and Control) is a less likely sub-category, but still possible as the paper mentions the proposed method can be extended to the supervised or unsupervised model for training deep structure networks, which could be relevant to control systems.
